spanGrp.span: ‘They were shut far in the mountain, the sheep were.
Jie-wa tsõ estee köte-lë-wa komĩ montaña jãrga ska obeja-wa tsõ köte-lë-wa (_)
A car carrying fruits goes by and [the fruits] fell down.
Pe karro kö-geũ-wã kalwö damĩ jargẽsã'
There they began to play; they just played.
jeska jie-wa ñã döwö-gẽ-wã jinõ jinõ Jie-wa jinõ-gẽ wakwa bö
The pigs were locked in and saw how the others were playing;
jeska kuchi yabla tsõ köte-lë-wa tsõ jie-wa sũã' mẽnẽbi jie-wa jinõ-gẽ bi
they wantes to play with the fruit; they played a lot.
Jie-wa jinã-gle kalwö wa jie-wa jino-gẽ tã'ĩ
The little pigs also wanted to play;
they could not/they were locked in and thus could not play with the others.
(_) jie-wa ka ĩã/ (_) jie-wa jie-wa tsõ köte-lë-wa ka ĩã jinẽr jie-wa ra
At that point, they helped. The were happy how to play with the comrades.
Je_juetara jie-wa í kime-gẽ jie-wa jie-wa ksër-gẽ-nẽ mẽnẽbi í siga-wa jinõ-gẽ je wa
Then they burst the house with that fruit.
Kea jie-wa të pe jũ… jũ kwã'-wã (_) je kalwö wa
Thus the man locked them in and they got sad.
Je kueinga pekaga të jie-wa kötie-gẽ-wã je wa (_) pekaga të jie-wa kötie-gẽ-wã ska jie-wa jẽr ianã'-wã
They wanted to play; the little pigs became sad.
Jie-wa jinã-gle kuchi yabla jẽr ianã'-wã
Then they went to play; they played.
Tögapa jie-wa mĩ-geu-lo-nẽ jinõ jeska í jinõ-gẽ
kea pato yabla tsõ ksër-gẽ-ka jiebi
The ducks saw how the pigs were playing and they became happy.
jie-wa sũẽ-gẽ-ite mẽnẽ jie-wa jinõ-gẽ bi pato yabla ksër-gẽ-ka
Jeme jie-wa jie-wa jie-wa õr-gẽ-wã todo
jie-wa ksër-gẽ-ka klabe mẽnẽ jie-wa jinõ bi
They wanted to keep playing but there were no more fruits to play with.
Jie-wa jie-wa jinã-gle ĩã pero ka ka kalwö ta ĩã jie-wa jinõ-glö
They were locked in really far but they were all happy.
Jie-wa tsõ köte-lë-wa komĩ' pe-wa jeska jie-wa jie-wa jinõ-gẽ jie-wa ksër-gẽ-ka klabe ñara rö
They went to hide from the people behind the trees.
Jebi jie-wa jie-wa mĩ-geu-lo mãĩ pe-wa kal kate ska ñã blö pe yiga
The people saw them break the window, so they went to hide;
Pe të jie-wa sũã' jie-wa të pe bidrio kwã'-wã jeska jie-wa mĩ-ge-ulo ñã blö
so the people were going to lock them in; they got sad because they wanted to keep playing.
Tögapa jie-wa pe të í kötie-gẽ-wã ska jie-wa jẽr ianã'-wã jie-wa jinã-gle-nẽ
There they were playing together and were happy till the end.’
Jeska jie-wa jinõ-gẽ-nẽ ñara (_) Kepa jie-wa të jie-wa ksër-gẽ-ka í õnã'-glö-wã ska rö
